<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>CowML Examples | Parse Mode</title>
        <script type="text/javascript" src="../src/cowml.js"></script>
        <script type="application/json" data-type="cowmlx">
            {
                "options" : {
                    "mode" : "update"
                },
                "schema" : {
                    "cow" : {
                        "type"          : "div",
                        "attributes"    : {
                            "onclick"       : "alert('Clicked a cow')"
                        },
                        "css"           : {
                            "display"       : "inline-block",
                            "border"        : "#000000 solid 4px",
                            "background"    : "#ffffff",
                            "padding"       : "8px",
                            "margin"        : "0 12px"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        </script>
    </head>
    <body bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
        <h1>Example: Parse Mode</h1>
        <hr />
        <p>By setting <code>options.mode</code> to <code>update</code> the original tag name will be preserved (<code>cow</code>).</p>
        <cow>I'm a cow!</cow>
    </body>
</html>